President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Greta C. Holtz, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, was nominated as Ambassador to the Sultanate of Oman. Alexander M. Laskaris, also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, was nominated as Ambassador to the Republic of Guinea. Allison M. Macfarlane, an associate professor of Environmental Science and Policy at George Mason University, was nominated as Commissioner of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission. Marcie B. Ries, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, was nominated as Ambassador to the Republic of Bulgaria. Walter M. Shaub, Jr., Deputy General Counsel of the U.S. Office of Government Ethics, was nominated as Director of the Office of Government Ethics. Additionally, President Obama announced his intent to appoint Fred P. Hochberg, President of the Export-Import Bank of the United States, as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars, and Earl W. Stafford, CEO of The Wentworth Group, as a member of the Presidentâ€™s Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities.